I want to bring in components from this repo: https://github.com/lizi-teo/ai-chat

Please do the following:

Clone or fetch the repo contents (you can use the GitHub URL directly)

Copy these folders into this project under src/ai-chat/:

components/primitives/ → src/ai-chat/components/primitives/
components/core/ → src/ai-chat/components/core/
components/layouts/ → src/ai-chat/components/layouts/
components/ui/ → src/ai-chat/components/ui/
lib/ → src/ai-chat/lib/
Install these packages (skip any already installed): pnpm install framer-motion @base-ui/react

Copy the CSS variables from the cloned repo's app/globals.css into this project's global CSS file. Only add the :root custom properties block — do not replace any existing styles.

Do NOT copy the cloned repo's package.json, vite.config, tsconfig, app/, or .storybook/ folders — this project's own config takes priority.

Import components like this: import { ChatWidget } from '@/ai-chat/components/layouts/ChatWidget/ChatWidget' import { CardStack } from '@/ai-chat/components/core/CardStack/CardStack' import { CardStrip } from '@/ai-chat/components/core/CardStrip/CardStrip'

Build a demo page showing ChatWidget in use.

The key things: namespace under src/ai-chat/ so nothing collides with your existing shadcn components, merge only the CSS variables (not the whole stylesheet), and skip all config files.